The paper deals with visual scene understanding, specifically depth estimation and scene parsing, which are tasks related to computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel multi-task learning approach, which involves deep learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of intermediate auxiliary tasks and multi-modal information, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper conducts experiments on challenging datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) aspects.
